    dc:creator "Ahrens, Dirk", "Pham, Phu Van", "Sabatinelli, Guido" ;
    dc:date "2024" ;
    dc:title "The genus Dedalopterus Sabatinelli & Pontuale, 1998 (Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae: Leucopholini) in Laos and Vietnam, with description of a new species" ;
    bibo:endPage "152" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2024-02-02" ;
    bibo:startPage "141" ;
    bibo:volume "5406" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10611469>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10611471>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10611473>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10611475>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10611477>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10611479> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10611469>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Dedalopterus lexuanhuei Pham, Ahrens and Sabatinelli, new species. Male (holotype, B–F, H, I) and female (paratype,A, G).A–B, pygidium; C, elytra in lateral view; D, G, head and pronotum; E, protibia; F, terminal maxillary palpomere; H, antenna; I, metatarsomeres. Scale bar: 2.0 mm, except for F=1.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10611469/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10611471>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Habitus in dorsal view. A–B, D. lexuanhuei Pham, Ahrens and Sabatinelli, new species. A, ♂ holotype; B, ♀ paratype; C–D, D. malyszi Bunalski, 2001 (Vietnam: Sa Pa; C, ♂; D, ♀). Scale bar: 5.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10611471/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10611473>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Male genitalia of Dedalopterus lexuanhuei Pham, Ahrens and Sabatinelli, new species (holotype,A–C); D. malyszi Bunalski, 2001 (D–F). A, D, parameres in left lateral view; B, E, parameres in dorsal view. C, F, parameres in right lateral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10611473/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10611475>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Lateral view of elytra (A–D), right lateral view of parameres tip (E–I). A, E, Dedalopterus malyszi Bunalski, 2001; B, G, D. pulchellus (paratype of D. bezdekorum Zídek & Krajčík, 2007); C, H, D. pulchellus Sabatinelli & Pontuale, 1998 (paratype of D. pulchellus); D, F, I, D. lexuanhuei Pham, Ahrens and Sabatinelli, new species (paratype)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10611475/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10611477>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Variation in male parameres of Dedalopterus pulchellus Sabatinelli & Pontuale, 1998 (A–J, all from Laos: Phu Phan). Scale bar: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10611477/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10611479>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Antennae, protibiae, and claws of Dedalopterus species.A, D, G, D. malyszi Bunalski, 2001; B, E, H, D. pulchellus (paratype of D. bezdekorum Zídek & Krajčík, 2007); C, F, I, D. lexuanhuei Pham, Ahrens and Sabatinelli, new species (paratype)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10611479/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

